  "": "Frustrated by the monotony of her mundane office job, Emma is searching for excitement and purpose in her life. Like her Type-A personality friends, Emma is a control freak looking for a sense of stability and security, but wrestling with her own mother's overbearing influence. She sells handmade jewelry online to supplement her income but insists that she is not doing it as a career.

When she meets Ryan, the charming coworker who sits across from her, he suddenly presents an opportunity for a new, committed relationship. Trying to assimilate into Ryan's world of hiking and camping, Emma clashes with his free-spirited friends whose carefree lifestyle threatens to upend their budding romance. Though the chemistry between the couple is undeniable, Emma's need for control and order may ultimately suffocate their relationship before it has a chance to flourish.

{
  "": "The Italian Countryside _ _ in the Thirties": while at a villa party in Tuscany, Alessia Rossini, a woman with many emotional issues, sees her husband, Dr. Leonardo Bianchi, a renowned psychologist, take an interest in a young and beautiful actress, Sophia De Santis. Jealousy gets the better of Alessia.
The story flashes back to how Leonardo and Alessia met. He was a respected psychologist who made the classic mistake of falling in love with his patient, Alessia Conti. He marries her despite warnings from his mentor, Dr. Marco Rossi, that it will ruin Leonardo's career.
Leonardo spends the next years of his life abandoning his work to indulge wife Alessia's many whims, leading a hedonistic life, paid for by Alessia's wealthy aunt, Countess Francesca. By the time he realizes the error of his ways and attempts to resume his career, it is Alessia who has found a new lover, and she wants a divorce.
